identificationRemarks: In the field, mature Mytilus trossulus can often be distinguished from M. galloprovincialis, M. edulis, and related hybrids by examing the siphon-mantle features of the live animal. Identification by shell shapes and sizes is otherwise inconclusive and remains limited to the level of species complex.
